EventItemActionText: This Communication was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections
EventItemTitle: Pursuant to §3-212(e) of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council of the City of New York and the Mayor are empowered to jointly appoint five members to serve on the New York City Lobbying Commission.  In addition, the Council and the Mayor jointly designate a Chair from among the Commission members.  The Council will consider the appointment of Herbert Berman as a member of the New York City Lobbying Commission and consider his designation as Chair.  If appointed, in conjunction with the Mayor, Mr. Berman will serve an undefined term.
EventItemMatterName: Herbert Berman, NYC Lobbying Commission

EventItemActionText: This Communication was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections
EventItemTitle: Pursuant to §3-212(e) of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council of the City of New York and the Mayor are empowered to jointly appoint five members to serve on the New York City Lobbying Commission.  In addition, the Council and the Mayor jointly designate a Chair from among the Commission members.  The Council will consider the appointment of Jamila Ponton Bragg as a member of the New York City Lobbying Commission.   If appointed, in conjunction with the Mayor, Ms. Ponton Bragg will serve an undefined term.
EventItemMatterName: Jamila Ponton Bragg, NYC  Lobbying Commission

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the purchase of New York state food.
EventItemMatterName: Purchase of New York state food.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to issue an annual report regarding hepatitis B and hepatitis C.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to issue an annual report regarding hepatitis B and hepatitis C.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the cleaning of liquid on a sidewalk, flagging or curbstone generated by trash placed curbside for collection and allowing the use of a hose to conduct such cleaning during times otherwise proscribed by such code.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the cleaning of liquid on a sidewalk, flagging or curbstone generated by trash placed curbside for collection and allowing the use of a hose to conduct such cleaning during times otherwise proscribed by such code.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring all pedestrian crossings with countdown signals to be equipped with an audible pedestrian signal.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all pedestrian crossings with countdown signals to be equipped with an audible pedestrian signal.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the reuse of tableware at consumer self-service operations.
EventItemMatterName: Reuse of tableware at consumer self-service operations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of landlords of multiple dwellings.
EventItemMatterName: Registration of landlords of multiple dwellings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the department of information technology and telecommunications to post certain information regarding street closures and parking regulations on the internet.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring DOITT to post certain information regarding street closures and parking regulations on the internet.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the publication of information regarding street fairs.
EventItemMatterName: The publication of information regarding street fairs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to clarifying the applicability of the noise control code.
EventItemMatterName: Clarifying the applicability of the noise control code.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to reinstate the privileges, formerly held by the Puerto Rican Resident Commissioner and other delegates, allowing them to vote on amendments and procedures in the Committee of the Whole.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to reinstate the privileges, formerly held by the Puerto Rican Resident Commissioner and other delegates, allowing them to vote on amendments and procedures in the Committee of the Whole.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing packaging reduction guidelines for contractors with city agencies.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing packaging reduction guidelines for contractors with city agencies.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the General Municipal Law to allow New York City to institute procurement preferences for the purchase of food originating within the New York region.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to amend the General Municipal Law to allow NYC to institute procurement preferences for the purchase of food originating within the NY region.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to enact legislation that regulates the amount and type of packaging used to encase goods procured by the State and all localities.
EventItemMatterName: Enact legislation that regulates the amount and type of packaging used to encase goods procured by the State and all localities.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the purchase and use of etching pens.
EventItemMatterName: Purchase and use of etching pens.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the fluoridation of water.
EventItemMatterName: Fluoridation of water.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to increase the punishment for endangering the welfare of a child by designating this crime as a felony.
EventItemMatterName: Increae the punishment for endangering the welfare of a child by designating this crime as a felony.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the Penal Law to make serial acts of public lewdness a class A misdemeanor offense, and to amend the Correction Law to include public lewdness as a registerable sex offense.
EventItemMatterName: Make serial acts of public lewdness a class A misdemeanor offense, and to amend the Correction Law to include public lewdness as a registerable sex offense.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to reintroduce and pass legislation that would require ex-felons to be fully informed of their voting rights.
EventItemMatterName: Reintroduce and pass legislation that would require ex-felons to be fully informed of their voting rights.

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Communication be Approved, by Council approved by Consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: Pursuant to §3-212(e) of the New York City Administrative Code, the Council of the City of New York and the Mayor are empowered to jointly appoint five members to serve on the New York City Lobbying Commission.  In addition, the Council and the Mayor jointly designate a Chair from among the Commission members.  The Council will consider the appointment of Herbert Berman as a member of the New York City Lobbying Commission and consider his designation as Chair.  If appointed, in conjunction with the Mayor, Mr. Berman will serve an undefined term.
EventItemMatterName: Herbert Berman, NYC Lobbying Commission
